summary:
Stresses the need to enhance predictability, sustainability, and flexibility of financing regional organizations undertaking peacekeeping under a UN mandate;

 Reiterates regional organizations' responsibility to secure resources, including through member contributions and partner support, and welcomes financial support provided by partners to African Union peacekeeping operations;

Requests the Secretary-General, in consultation with the African Union, to conduct a comprehensive analysis of lessons learned from practical cooperation between the UN and African Union;

Requests the Secretary-General to include assessments of progress on cooperation between the UN and regional organizations in his regular reporting to the Security Council;

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
